        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 21 at 1:24PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>Scattered thunderstorms will continue moving east along the Hi-
Line through at least the middle of this afternoon. These storms
are producing cloud-to-ground lightning, brief heavy rainfall,
wind gusts to 40 mph, and small hail or graupel.

These storms may also produce brief cold air funnels, which are
mostly harmless. However, if they briefly touch down as
landspouts, they may cause even stronger winds gusts or possibly
some minor damage to trees or structures. If you spot either of
these, move indoors, and we would appreciate if you could report
your sighting to the National Weather Service.
</description>
